This test sets the partner sterilization factor equal to (-1*baseline) in the medium condom equation among marrieds, and making all females sterilized which should have the effect of reducing medium condom intender to zero.
Pregnancy Outcome Poor Birth 4m: Cross Check of Baseline Factor for Poor Births among Marrieds_2
This test sets all covariates in the unmarried poor birth equation equal extremely high values, which should have no effect on pregnancy outcomes among marrieds.
Coital Frequency High Coital Thresholds: Check of Unmarried High CoitFreq Thresholds _0

This test assigns all unmarried agents to the high coitfreq category and then sets the Minimum and Maximum thresholds for that category equal to 1, which should result in agents having the same amount of sex (this test is probably redundant).
Coital Frequency Low Coit Threshold None Married: Check of Married Low CoitFreq Thresholds _1

This test assigns all married agents to the low coitfreq category and then sets the Minimum and Maximum thresholds for that category equal to zero, which should result in nobody having sex in the model.
Contraception Pill 2: Spot Check of Covariates Pill Equation Among Unmarrieds _0
This test sets all age factors equal to (-1*baseline) in the equation among unmarrieds, which should have the effect of eliminating pill use in the simulation.
